File: President Cyril Ramaphosa chairing a virtual Presidential Coordinating Council (PCC) meeting from his private residence in Johannesburg. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to chair two virtual meetings. Ramaphosa will chair meetings with the President's Coordinating Council and the Nedlac as the national state of disaster is extended to15 October. The President's Coordinating Council meeting will be attended by his deputy, David Mabuza, various ministers and premiers. Government, business and labour have been meeting over the last few weeks to develop a united approach to rebuilding the economy. This is in response to the coronavirus pandemic. READ: Denosa calls for Ramaphosa intervention Ramaphosa is expected to brief the nation this week. It's speculated that the president will relax the lockdown further to level 1. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.